        <title>KMT-2024-BLG-0816/OGLE-2024-BLG-0519 -- A Microlensing Event with Candidate Free-Floating Planet Lens and Blended Light</title>
            <categories>astro-ph.EP astro-ph.GA</categories>
            <comments>submitted; 18 pages, 6 figures</comments>
            <license>http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/4.0/</license>
            <abstract>We present the discovery of a free-floating planet microlensing event KMT-2024-BLG-0816. The event shows finite-source effect, significant blending light, and no microlensing signal from a putative planet host. Among the free-floating planet events with finite source effects, this is the only event with unresolved blending light. We discuss how follow-up observations can be used to determine whether the blending light originates from a putative planet host.</abstract>
